Reasoning: The paper deals with sentiment analysis and classification of posts on social media related to abuse and mental health. This falls under the domain of natural language processing (NLP) and social media analysis, which are covered under the sub-categories of cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Additionally, the paper uses hand-crafted features to train the model, which falls under the sub-category of cs.CY (Computers and Society). The use of images in the analysis suggests the involvement of computer vision, which is covered under the sub-categories of cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
